This paper deals with the development of a computational framework for solving fully coupled electromagneto-thermomechanical systems undergoing large deformations. The paper discusses the use of advanced computational tools and presents an open-source implementation using the FEniCS package. The paper is likely to be categorized under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as it deals with the development of a computational framework for solving engineering problems. It could also be categorized under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software) as it discusses the use of numerical methods and software tools. The paper also deals with the computation of electromagnetic fields, which could lead to categorization under cs.EM (Electromagnetism) and cs.CM (Classical Physics).
